<item>
  <title>Chain Cloud: A decentralized copyright trading platform</title>
  <dc:creator>Zhiqing Ma</dc:creator>
  <link>https://drganghe.github.io/quarto-academic-website-template/posts/projects/chainCloud/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p><img src="https://drganghe.github.io/quarto-academic-website-template/files/images/structure.png" class="img-fluid" style="width:90.0%"></p>
<p>• Key platform features include: blockchain-based copyright evidence storage, smart contract-driven copyright transactions, multidimensional data analytics and visualization, regulatory auditing, and traceability queries.</p>
<p>• Blockchain: Developed smart contract chain codes based on <strong>Hyperledger Fabric</strong> to implement copyright evidence storage, automated transaction execution, and revenue distribution logic, ensuring tamper-proof and fully traceable transaction data.</p>
<p>• Data Storage: Designed a hybrid storage architecture storing critical transaction hashes on-chain while managing business data off-chain via <strong>MySQL</strong> and storing image/document files using <strong>Huawei Cloud OBS</strong>, balancing performance and security requirements.</p>
<p>• Backend: Designed and implemented the backend architecture for a blockchain-based smart copyright trading platform. Built high-performance RESTful APIs using <strong>Golang + Hertz</strong> microservices framework to support core functions including copyright registration on-chain, transaction execution, and regulatory review. Implemented a comprehensive permission control system encompassing user registration/login, JWT authentication, and regulatory review. Utilized WebSocket calls to large models for AI-assisted Q&amp;A.</p>
<p><a href="https://b23.tv/ixS4DDp"><img src="https://drganghe.github.io/quarto-academic-website-template/files/images/project1.png" class="img-fluid" style="width:90.0%"></a></p>
<p>(Click the image to view the project introduction video submitted for the competition)</p>
<p>17TH SHANGHAI UNIVERSITY COMPUTER APPLICATION CONTEST Second Prize | Jun 2025</p>
