<item>
  <title>Holistic Ecosystem Dynamics with Lampreys Considering Age Structure and Diffusion Terms</title>
  <dc:creator>Junjie Pu, Sheng Li, Zhiqing Ma</dc:creator>
  <link>https://drganghe.github.io/quarto-academic-website-template/posts/projects/model/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p><img src="https://drganghe.github.io/quarto-academic-website-template/files/images/lamprey_model_workFlow.png" class="img-fluid" style="width:90.0%"></p>
<p>• Key project features include: quantification of sex ratio functions, simulation of parasite diffusion using spectral methods, and a robust numerical solver for non-trivial equilibrium systems.</p>
<p>• <strong>Data Analysis &amp; Pre-processing</strong>: Cleaned historical observation data and quantified the key “sex ratio function” by conducting comparative analysis between <strong>Polynomial Regression</strong> and <strong>SVM (Support Vector Machines)</strong>, establishing the statistical foundation for the ecosystem model.</p>
<p>• <strong>Core Simulation Engine</strong>: Designed and implemented a solver based on the <strong>Finite Difference Method</strong> to handle the complex ODE-PDE coupling model. Introduced the <strong>Dirac Delta function</strong> to accurately mathematically express biological pulses within the ecosystem.</p>
<p>• <strong>Optimization &amp; Stability</strong>: Implemented the <strong>Levenberg-Marquardt algorithm</strong> and <strong>Trust Domain Policy Optimization (TRPO)</strong> to solve for non-trivial equilibrium, ensuring numerical convergence where traditional black-box tools failed. Applied the <strong>Chebyshev spectral method</strong> to simulate the diffusion effect of parasites with high accuracy.</p>
<p><a href="../../..\files/pdf/2403047.pdf"><img src="https://drganghe.github.io/quarto-academic-website-template/files/images/lamprey_model_ecosystem.png" class="img-fluid" style="width:90.0%"></a></p>
<p>(Click the image to view the technical paper)</p>
<p><strong>MCM/ICM (Mathematical Contest in Modeling)</strong> Meritorious Winner (First Prize) | Apr 2024</p>
